CSS selectors:
-- stands for cascading styling sheet
-- it is another way of locating elements uniquely
-- CSS does not allow you to identify an element by text

    Syntax:
    -- tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']
    example: input[id = 'user-message']

    Shortcuts for CSS:
    1. classname -> "."
        -- tagname.classNameValue
        example: input.form-control
    2. ID -> "#"
        -- tagname#.idValue
        example: input#ctl00_MainContent_username

    Contains method in CSS:
    -- * symbol represents contains() method
    -- tagname[attribute *= 'partial attribute value']
    example: input[id *= 'username']

    starts-with method in CSS:
    -- ^ symbol represents starts-with method
    -- tagname[attribute ^= 'starting attribute value']
    example: input[type ^= 'sub']

    ends-with method in CSS:
    -- $ symbol represents ends-with method
    -- tagname[attribute $= 'ending attribute value']
    example: input[id $= 'password']

WebElement Commands:
-- consist of several mehtods where we can perform actions and get element state on webpage

    isEnabled() -- boolean value
    isSelected() -- boolean value
    isDisplayed() -- boolean value
    clear() -- void
    getText() -- String
    getAttribute() -- String